  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Village Club du Soleil is a great option if you are looking for an inclusive ski holiday in <a data-udi="umb://document/4355b275387942f08b2416ccd4bee606" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4355b275387942f08b2416ccd4bee606}" title="Montgenevre">Montgenèvre</a>. Your lift pass, ski or snowboard hire with boots and full board meals are included in the holiday price. Plus your children can make new found friends in the children's clubs. There is also daily entertainment to keep you occupied, even off of the slopes. </p>
<h2>Location</h2>
<p>Nestled on the border with Italy, the hotel is serviced by the Montquitaine chairlift just 150m from the property, providing incredible access to the ski area. The free hotel shuttle bus also takes you to <a data-udi="umb://document/4355b275387942f08b2416ccd4bee606" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4355b275387942f08b2416ccd4bee606}" title="Montgenevre">Montgenèvre</a> resort centre between 8:30 and 16:30, this service is extended to 19:45 on Tuesday and Thursday.</p>
<h2>Inclusive ski hotel</h2>
<p>When you book a holiday at the Village Club du Soleil, all of the essentials for your snow sports trip are included - a six day lift pass (includes two days in the <a data-udi="umb://document/ac18b1d87c81457eaf0af66a3b8f0b19" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ac18b1d87c81457eaf0af66a3b8f0b19}" title="Milky Way Ski Area">Milky Way</a> and one day in <a data-udi="umb://document/b7e31f4645514434bec76a3728e974c0" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b7e31f4645514434bec76a3728e974c0}" title="Serre Chevalier">Serre Chevalier</a>), standard skis or snowboard and boots, child helmet hire, full board dining including lunches and wine, children's clubs, evening entertainment and much more. If you're wanting lunch on the mountains then there is the option to pre-order a picnic - otherwise you can return to the hotel and enjoy a varied buffet lunch.</p>
<h2>Kids clubs </h2>
<p>During your stay, your children age 4 months to 17 years can make new friends at the exclusive kids clubs which run throughout the season - certain clubs are only available during French school holidays, however there is still plenty to keep the whole family occupied. </p>
<p>For children from 2-4 years (Club des Babyz) are included in the mornings with music, drama, creative games, and reading. The club runs from 8.30am to 6pm and also 7pm to 9pm.</p>
<p>For children from 4-6 years (Club des Hapyz) and 6-11 years (Club des Kidz), activities may include igloo making, sledging, snow shoeing and creative games. The club runs from 8:30am to 6pm and also 7pm to 9pm during French school holidays (outside of the holidays this club runs in the afternoon). Ski tuition is not included and is available to pre-book.</p>
<p>Club La Ruche is for teenagers from 11-17 years and runs from 9:30am to 9pm. The morning is spent skiing and in the afternoon they have a varied programme of activities, with music and dancing in the evening.</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
